George Morris (April 1833 – 11 September 1912) was an Irish Home Rule League politician.
He was first elected as Member of Parliament (MP) for Galway Borough at a by-election in 1867, but did not stand again in 1868. He returned to the seat in 1874, but again did not stand in 1880.He was High Sheriff of Galway Town in 1860.
